213
00:14:37,147 --> 00:14:39,548
[SPEAKER_06]: I was just going to ask you to clarify this.

214
00:14:39,568 --> 00:15:02,433
[SPEAKER_02]: The moving to work is what we had applied for where we are developing an asset assistance or the asset development program for residents where the Housing Authority is going to do primarily two things at this point and that is to contribute to a bank account to a resident and be able to report

215
00:15:03,034 --> 00:15:09,156
[SPEAKER_02]: the success that that resident has in paying their rent in an effort to increase their credit worthiness.

216
00:15:09,936 --> 00:15:17,479
[SPEAKER_02]: We're meeting almost on a weekly basis with the folks from HUD in developing this moving to work.

217
00:15:18,019 --> 00:15:21,700
[SPEAKER_02]: The significance of moving to work also though is it creates some fungibility.

218
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:31,505
[SPEAKER_02]: as far as the Housing Authority to be able to move monies that were previously dedicated in Section 8 into public housing and public housing into Section 8.

219
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:36,327
[SPEAKER_02]: But this is an effort for us to begin to outreach to the residents.

220
00:15:36,687 --> 00:15:42,310
[SPEAKER_02]: There's a now with the award for us and 18 other housing authorities who submitted

221
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:45,732
[SPEAKER_02]: an application for this that the board had approved previously.

222
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:53,878
[SPEAKER_02]: We're one of 126 moving-to-work agencies out of anywhere between 3,500 and 4,000 housing authorities in the nation.

223
00:15:54,398 --> 00:15:55,599
[SPEAKER_02]: So it's resident-based.

224
00:15:55,999 --> 00:16:04,485
[SPEAKER_02]: The reason why this amendment is here is because the annual contributions contract is that contract which HUD enters into with the housing authority.

225
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:09,868
[SPEAKER_02]: And so this amendment actually adds to the original annual contribution contract.

226
00:16:10,369 --> 00:16:12,310
[SPEAKER_02]: It's a HUD requirement for us to execute.

