231
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:46,171
[SPEAKER_04]: Is this a program created through HUD?

232
00:16:46,491 --> 00:17:00,382
[SPEAKER_02]: Moving to work is a whole separate agenda that HUD has, and they have what they call cohorts within that, and this is, I believe this is called the fourth cohort, and we haven't applied previously, but we've applied at this point in time.

233
00:17:00,862 --> 00:17:22,247
[SPEAKER_02]: And the main motivation for us to do this, I should say the secondary motivation for us to do this beyond that of assisting the residents, was because this will more than likely benefit us going forward with the construction of this building based upon the fungibility that we would have and the ability that we may have to affirmatively impact the rents that are here.

234
00:17:23,506 --> 00:17:24,947
[SPEAKER_02]: But moving to work is just that.

235
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:30,331
[SPEAKER_02]: It's been around for, I'm going to say, at least ten years.

236
00:17:30,651 --> 00:17:32,293
[SPEAKER_02]: Kayleen, maybe a little bit more.

237
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:33,494
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah.

238
00:17:33,694 --> 00:17:37,136
[SPEAKER_02]: And what it was, was an initiative to move these residents to work.

239
00:17:37,717 --> 00:17:37,957
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay.

240
00:17:38,697 --> 00:17:38,858
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah.

241
00:17:39,098 --> 00:17:39,338
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay.

242
00:17:40,719 --> 00:17:51,107
[SPEAKER_02]: If I had a choice out of the cohorts, this is the one that I would have wanted to participate in and was, simply because of the direct benefit it will pose to the residents.

243
00:17:54,937 --> 00:17:57,241
[SPEAKER_02]: And just one supplement to that.

244
00:17:58,162 --> 00:18:03,631
[SPEAKER_02]: One of the suggestions that HUD has raised is to just provide $10 a month to the residents.

245
00:18:05,862 --> 00:18:09,585
