334
00:26:27,312 --> 00:26:27,612
[SPEAKER_01]: Sure.

335
00:26:28,453 --> 00:26:28,553
[SPEAKER_01]: So

336
00:26:30,454 --> 00:26:42,337
[SPEAKER_01]: As Jeff probably mentioned, a key part of the financing for the renovations of Saltonstall Apartments is the low-income housing tax credits that the project will receive.

337
00:26:43,198 --> 00:26:49,720
[SPEAKER_01]: And in order to get an economic benefit of that, you need to have an investor who purchases the credits.

338
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:56,522
[SPEAKER_01]: And so the MHA put out a request for proposal on July 7, seeking

339
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:05,067
[SPEAKER_01]: both lenders for the project, but also the tax credit investor, which is what today's memo is about.

340
00:27:06,972 --> 00:27:14,196
[SPEAKER_01]: It was a challenging process to get an equity investor on board for the project for multiple reasons.

341
00:27:15,296 --> 00:27:20,299
[SPEAKER_01]: It's been a challenging year overall for equity investment.

342
00:27:20,899 --> 00:27:30,224
[SPEAKER_01]: A lot of the big investors had already signed up all of their money for this year, and that was partially due to the fact that

343
00:27:31,616 --> 00:27:36,462
[SPEAKER_01]: Projects that were supposed to close last year ended up closing this year.

344
00:27:37,423 --> 00:27:39,927
[SPEAKER_01]: And they also had staffing shortages.

345
00:27:40,287 --> 00:27:48,578
[SPEAKER_01]: And as you know, interest rates have been going up, which changes the calculation of how much the interest rates are worth.

346
00:27:51,059 --> 00:28:08,747
[SPEAKER_01]: The other item was that because it's a very large project, you either need to get a very big bank to provide a direct placement, or you need someone who is willing to work with multiple investors to pool them.

347
00:28:09,648 --> 00:28:16,371
[SPEAKER_01]: And that meant that a lot of investors were too small to invest in this project.

348
00:28:17,271 --> 00:28:18,212
[SPEAKER_01]: And then finally,

349
00:28:19,925 --> 00:28:36,759
[SPEAKER_01]: One of the challenges was that, you know, although the MHA team has a lot of significant executive experience, the housing authority as a whole has not done a low-income housing tax credit project before.

350
00:28:38,060 --> 00:28:47,348
[SPEAKER_01]: And investors, given the fact that there, it was a challenging year to get funding really focused on the projects where there were more

351
00:28:47,882 --> 00:28:51,848
[SPEAKER_01]: There was more experience with low-income housing tax credit projects.

352
00:28:53,210 --> 00:29:01,302
[SPEAKER_01]: So essentially what we did was we engaged in direct conversations with investors who had said,

353
00:29:02,550 --> 00:29:04,873
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, we're interested in this project.

354
00:29:05,894 --> 00:29:25,173
[SPEAKER_01]: We know that this is a really fantastic opportunity, but we have these concerns around the lack of LIHTC experience and the lack of having a balance sheet that has sufficient unrestricted cash to provide guarantees for the project.

355
00:29:26,422 --> 00:29:29,123
[SPEAKER_01]: And out of those, we spoke with a limited group.

356
00:29:30,183 --> 00:29:37,605
[SPEAKER_01]: And out of those, the investors that we're recommending today, Enterprise, came out the next August.

357
00:29:38,945 --> 00:29:42,946
[SPEAKER_01]: And so just to give you a little bit of background about Enterprise.

358
00:29:43,586 --> 00:29:47,107
[SPEAKER_01]: So Enterprise is a non-profit.

359
00:29:47,667 --> 00:29:48,828
[SPEAKER_01]: They're based in Maryland.

360
00:29:49,668 --> 00:29:53,209
[SPEAKER_01]: They're a non-profit that has a mission of expanding affordable housing.

361
00:29:55,557 --> 00:30:07,947
[SPEAKER_01]: but one of the things that it has is it has a subsidiary that works with investors to find investors to buy low-income housing tax credits for projects like Saltonstall.

362
00:30:09,448 --> 00:30:20,016
[SPEAKER_01]: And there are also a, so I am a senior project manager at the Cambridge Housing Authority, one of the development consultants working

363
00:30:20,649 --> 00:30:31,714
[SPEAKER_01]: on Saltonstall, and I have experience working with them before on Cambridge Housing Authority projects, and we found that they are a very good partner to work with.

364
00:30:34,876 --> 00:30:42,299
[SPEAKER_01]: So that brings us now to the stage where it says analysis of enterprise equity proposals.

